.TH SDL_HintCallback 3type "SDL 3.1.3" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 DATATYPES"
.SH NAME
SDL_HintCallback \- A callback used to send notifications of hint value changes\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_hints\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "typedef void(SDLCALL *SDL_HintCallback)(void *userdata, const char *name, const char *oldValue, const char *newValue);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is called an initial time during

.BR SDL_AddHintCallback
 with the hint's current value,
and then again each time the hint's value changes\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I userdata
what was passed as
.BR userdata
to 
.BR SDL_AddHintCallback
()\[char46]
.TP
.I name
what was passed as
.BR name
to 
.BR SDL_AddHintCallback
()\[char46]
.TP
.I oldValue
the previous hint value\[char46]
.TP
.I newValue
the new value hint is to be set to\[char46]
.SH THREAD SAFETY
This callback is fired from whatever thread is setting a new hint value\[char46]
SDL holds a lock on the hint subsystem when calling this callback\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This datatype is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

